This paper deals with the task of finding lexical substitutes, which is a common problem in natural language processing. The paper proposes a new search algorithm that is efficient and exact, making it relevant to several sub-categories of computer science. Specifically, it could be categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves finding substitutes for words, cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it uses language models, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves language understanding, and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as it addresses the computational complexity of the problem.
